.TH "tomoyo_check_path_acl" 9 "tomoyo_check_path_acl" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tomoyo_check_path_acl \- Check permission for path operation.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" tomoyo_check_path_acl
.BI "(struct tomoyo_request_info *r "  ","
.BI "const struct tomoyo_acl_info *ptr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "r" 12
Pointer to "struct tomoyo_request_info".
.IP "ptr" 12
Pointer to "struct tomoyo_acl_info".
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns true if granted, false otherwise.

To be able to use wildcard for domain transition, this function sets
matching entry on success. Since the caller holds \fBtomoyo_read_lock\fP,
it is safe to set matching entry.
